{"title_page": "Charles Villeneuve", "text_new": "{{ infobox person\n| name        = Charles Villeneuve\n| birth_name  = Charles Leroy\n| image       = Ludovic_Giuly_et_Charles_Villeneuve_au_Camp_des_Loges.jpg\n| caption     = Villeneuve (right) with PSG player [[Ludovic Giuly]]\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1941|07|19|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Beirut]], [[Lebanon]]\n| nationality = [[France|French]]\n| occupation  = [[Television journalist]]\n}}\n\n'''Charles Villeneuve''' (born '''Charles Leroy''';<ref>{{cite news |title=Charles Villeneuve nomm\u00e9 pr\u00e9sident du PSG |trans-title=Charles Villeneuve named president of PSG|url=https://www.lemonde.fr/sport/article/2008/05/27/charles-villeneuve-nomme-president-du-psg_1050508_3242.html |accessdate=4 November 2018 |work=Le Monde |agency=AFP |date=27 May 2008 |language=French}}</ref> 19 July 1941) is a French journalist.\n\nHe was the sports director of the television channel [[TF1]].<ref name=figaro>{{cite news |title=Charles Villeneuve  aux commandes du PSG|trans-title=Charles Villeneuve in command of PSG |url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/sport/2008/05/27/02001-20080527ARTFIG00579-charles-villeneuve-aux-commandes-du-psg.php |accessdate=4 November 2018 |work=Le Figaro |date=27 May 2008 |language=French}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 May 2008, he was named as [[List of Paris Saint-Germain F.C. presidents|president]] of [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.]] ahead of the new season, after the one-month interim of [[Simon Tahar]]; PSG had narrowly avoided relegation from [[Ligue 1]].<ref name=figaro/> He was the third journalist to hold the post, after [[Michel Denisot]] and [[Charles Bi\u00e9try]] in the 1990s.<ref name=figaro/>\n\nIn January 2009, he wrote a letter to the club's board in which he criticised their lack of investment. The letter was leaked to ''[[Le Parisien]]''. He was then dismissed by owners [[Colony Capital]], whose president [[S\u00e9bastien Bazin]] took that position at the club.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Lyttleton |first1=Ben |title=Boardroom blitz leaves PSG shaky |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/blog/2009/jan/20/ben-lyttleton-france-football-villeneuve |accessdate=4 November 2018 |work=The Guardian |date=20 January 2009}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Paris Saint-Germain F.C. presidents}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Villeneuve, Charles}}\n[[Category:1941 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Beirut]]\n[[Category:French male journalists]]\n[[Category:French television journalists]]\n[[Category:French television presenters]]\n[[Category:20th-century French journalists]]\n[[Category:21st-century French journalists]]\n[[Category:Paris Saint-Germain F.C. non-playing staff]]\n[[Category:French football chairmen and investors]]\n[[Category:French people of Armenian descent]]\n\n\n{{France-journalist-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{ infobox Person\n| name        = Charles Villeneuve\n| birth_name  = Charles Leroy\n| image       = Ludovic_Giuly_et_Charles_Villeneuve_au_Camp_des_Loges.jpg\n| caption     = Villeneuve (right) with PSG player [[Ludovic Giuly]]\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1941|07|19|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Beirut]], [[Lebanon]]\n| nationality = [[France|French]]\n| occupation  = [[Television journalist]]\n}}\n\n'''Charles Villeneuve''' (born '''Charles Leroy''';<ref>{{cite news |title=Charles Villeneuve nomm\u00e9 pr\u00e9sident du PSG |trans-title=Charles Villeneuve named president of PSG|url=https://www.lemonde.fr/sport/article/2008/05/27/charles-villeneuve-nomme-president-du-psg_1050508_3242.html |accessdate=4 November 2018 |work=Le Monde |agency=AFP |date=27 May 2008 |language=French}}</ref> 19 July 1941) is a French journalist.\n\nHe was the sports director of the television channel [[TF1]].<ref name=figaro>{{cite news |title=Charles Villeneuve  aux commandes du PSG|trans-title=Charles Villeneuve in command of PSG |url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/sport/2008/05/27/02001-20080527ARTFIG00579-charles-villeneuve-a